Chicken Bacon Ranch Quesadillas are love ❤️ —————————————————————————————————————— Starting out by marinating your chicken however you like. I chose my blackened marinade that I use for my Sous vide chicken. Sear off you chicken in a cast iron pan or a flat top. Just want to get some great color on them. You can then either cook them Sous vide at 155 for an hour and hold till your ready or pop them in the oven to finish Once you’ve cooked your chicken and bacon, cut them into manageable pieces so that they’ll go into your quesadilla. Heat my griddle to 375 and put down a layer of butter. Sauté a half of a diced sweet onion and bell pepper. You can even throw a Serrano in there. Once the veggies are done move them over to the side and put another small spoon of butter down. Next goes your tortilla shell. On one side you put down a layer of cheese, chicken, bacon, veggies, and ranch. Cover with a tad more cheese and close the other half. Once the first side is golden brown flip and repeat with the other side. . .
